# Task 3: Heart Disease Prediction

## 📌 Objective
Build a classification model to predict whether a person is at risk of heart disease based on health data.

## 📊 Dataset
- **Source:** Heart Disease UCI Dataset (Kaggle)
- **Samples:** 920 patients
- **Features:** 13 medical attributes
- **Target:** Binary (0 = No Disease, 1 = Disease)

## 🛠️ Tools Used
- Python (pandas, numpy)
- Visualization (matplotlib, seaborn)
- Machine Learning (scikit-learn)

## 🤖 Models Compared
1. **Logistic Regression** - Accuracy: 84.2%, ROC-AUC: 0.903
2. **Decision Tree** - Accuracy: 77.7%, ROC-AUC: 0.854

## 🔍 Key Findings
- **Best Model:** Logistic Regression (84.2% accuracy)
- **Top Risk Factors:** 
  - Atypical chest pain
  - ST depression (oldpeak)
  - Number of blocked vessels (ca)
  - Exercise-induced angina (exang)
- **Demographic Insights:**
  - Males: 63.2% have heart disease
  - Females: 25.8% have heart disease
  - Average age (disease): 55.9 years

## 📈 Performance Metrics
| Model | Accuracy | ROC-AUC | CV Score |
|-------|----------|---------|----------|
| Logistic Regression | 84.2% | 0.903 | 0.812 |
| Decision Tree | 77.7% | 0.854 | 0.758 |

